The fundamental physical principles of modern technologies are introduced. The potential teachers acquire an ability to teach the elective course "Physics and engineering" at the high school (gymnasium) level.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The main goal of the course is to explain the fundamental physical principles of modern technologies and provide potential teachers with the skills to teach the elective course "Physics and Engineering" at the secondary school level.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of this course, the student should be able to: 1. Know the basic definitions in the field of the modern physical and technological concept of the world within the limits of the vocabulary available via the web support of the course; 2. Explain the functional principles of some technological materials and devices within the limits of the program of the elective course "Physics and Engineering", applying physical terminology in a correct way; 3. Compile an overview representing the functional principles of an important technological material or device, and make a public presentation of this overview.
